         <entry xml:id="diqratos-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#diqinton-dlgenr"
                next="#decumani-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">דיקרטוס</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dyqrṭws</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">diqraṭos</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">adjective</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1 Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דיקרטוס</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דיקרטום</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דקרטיס</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="diqratos-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>tied (at the feet)</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Classical Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>δίκροτος</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>[והנחש היה ערום מכל חית וגו'] ר' הושעיא רבה אמר דיקריטיס היה עומד כקנה ורגלים יש לו</quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">19,1</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 171: 1</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>Now the serpent was more subtle than any beast of the field (Gen 3,1). R.Hoshaʿyaʾ the Elder said: He stood tied like a reed at his feet.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">= <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">GenRbti 41</bibl>
                  </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note anchored="true">
         MY renders Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">διάκριτος</term>. See <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 402b</bibl>, but Fleischer in <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 442b</bibl> renders Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">δικεράστος</term>. Löw in Krauss ad loc. interprets as Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">διρέκτος</term> (rejected in MY).
      </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Krauss, LW II</title>
                  <citedRange>212a</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
